- id: PAT-SCRIBE-AGENT-POOL-COORDINATION-001
  date: 2026-05-28
  schema_patch_date: 2026-05-28
  tier: hot
  status: ACTIVE
  titre: Agent-pool terminal coordination
  l0_abstract: Four terminals must start as interchangeable idle agents with unique runtime identity; they claim semantic work only when a concrete task arrives, and shared files require re-read/rebase instead of exclusion.
  scope: dev-bundle/multi-agent
  approved: true
  evidence:
    type: OBSERVED
    source: JOURNAL-SCRIBE-AGENT-POOL-COORDINATION-20260528
    observable: init-tenor, live-coordination, workflow status and AGENTS rules were aligned to dynamic identity, idle presence, semantic claims, and no fixed four-agent gate.
  regle_operationnelle:
    - Start each terminal with `scribe whoami --type cli --surface idle` and use the returned session ID.
    - Run `scribe coordination status` before work and take `scribe coordination claim` only for a concrete task.
    - Same file across different semantic claims is allowed only after re-reading current files and rebasing before delivery.
    - Same semantic claim, exact function, deletion, rename, or global refactor requires coordination.
    - "`workflow status --required ... --strict` is only for an explicit named gate, never the default pool model."
  liens_causaux:
    source: JOURNAL-SCRIBE-AGENT-POOL-COORDINATION-20260528
  confirmed_sessions:
  - session: JOURNAL-SCRIBE-AGENT-POOL-COORDINATION-20260528
    observable: User explicitly asked to engrave the terminal agent-pool coordination decision into SCRIBE after protocol alignment.
- id: PAT-SCRIBE-STRICT-CAUSAL-DENSITY-001
  date: 2026-05-29
  schema_patch_date: 2026-05-29
  tier: hot
  status: ACTIVE
  titre: Dashboard causal density is informational
  l0_abstract: Do not create SCAR/GHOST/PAT to clean dashboard ratios; write causal memory only after real pain, bugs, durable decisions, or rejected alternatives.
  scope: dev-bundle/memory-governance
  approved: true
  evidence:
    type: OBSERVED
    source: JOURNAL-STRICT-CAUSAL-DENSITY-POLICY-20260529
    observable: User accepted TORVALDS recommendation and dashboard docs were patched to keep strict causal memory.
  regle_operationnelle:
  - Treat causal-density P2 as a reminder, not mandatory write work.
  - Leave the warning visible when no concrete future pain exists.
  - Create SCAR/GHOST/PAT only for real bug, real decision, proven rejected alternative, or durable project pain.
  liens_causaux:
    source: GHOST-SCRIBE-STRICT-MEMORY-001
- id: PAT-SCRIBE-PAIN-CAPTURE-REFLEX-001
  date: 2026-06-16
  schema_patch_date: 2026-06-16
  tier: hot
  status: ACTIVE
  titre: Real pain must become an immediately reusable SCAR
  l0_abstract: >
    Do not chase causal-density ratios, but any resolved bug after more than two attempts, regression, costly rollback, or broken browser/visual smoke must be recorded immediately as a SCAR with cause_racine, resolution, and test_binding; before adjacent future work, retrieve and challenge against that memory.
  scope: dev-bundle/memory-governance
  approved: true
  evidence:
    type: REASONED
    source: JOURNAL-SCRIBE-PAIN-CAPTURE-REFLEX-20260616
    observable: User rejected cosmetic ratio chasing and requested a host-LLM reflex that engraves real pain immediately and retrieves scars before similar work.
  regle_operationnelle:
  - Bug resolved after more than two attempts => SCAR immediately, not journal-only.
  - Regression, costly rollback, or broken browser/visual smoke => SCAR immediately with test_binding.
  - SCAR must include cause_racine, resolution, test_binding, and attention_future when relevant.
  - Before a task near a known scar, run scribe-rag query/explain/challenge so the memory is exploited at decision time.
  - Never create SCAR/GHOST/PAT solely to improve a causal-density ratio.
  liens_causaux:
  - PAT-SCRIBE-STRICT-CAUSAL-DENSITY-001
  - INV-F003
