- id: DEBT-BOLLINGER-SOURCE-OFFSET-001
  priorite: P2
  titre: Bollinger Source and Offset controls must affect math/rendering
  date: '2026-05-12'
  l0_abstract: Les settings Bollinger exposent source et offset, mais le calcul actuel consomme seulement length/multiplier
    et le rendu ne décale pas encore les séries.
  impact: 'Risque UX: contrôle visible sans effet réel; parité TradingView incomplète.'
  resolution_attendue: Brancher source dans calculateBollinger/worker et appliquer offset aux séries ECharts, ou masquer ces
    contrôles jusqu'au câblage complet.
  status: RESOLVED
  tier: warm
  schema_patch_date: '2026-05-26'
  scope: technical-analysis
  plan_remboursement: Revalider la dette importée lors du prochain chantier touchant cette surface; soit créer un ticket de
    correction, soit archiver si elle est obsolète.
  resolution_effective: >
    Vérification du 2026-05-29: calculateBollinger consomme source et offset, le worker transmet bollingerSettings.source
    et bollingerSettings.offset, et le renderer autorise la projection des bandes Bollinger quand offset est positif.
    La recommandation dashboard était donc une dette active obsolète, pas un bug applicatif courant.
  status_log:
  - date: '2026-05-29'
    from: ACTIVE
    to: RESOLVED
    raison: >
      Le code courant prouve que les contrôles Bollinger Source et Offset sont déjà câblés dans le calcul worker et dans
      le rendu ECharts; garder cette dette ACTIVE maintenait une fausse action P1 dans le dashboard SCRIBE.
    session: JOURNAL-BOLLINGER-DEBT-TRUTH-20260529
lecons: []
journal:
- id: JOURNAL-SCRIBE-TENOR-INIT-MACHINE-PROOF-20260616
  date: 2026-06-16
  mode: CRITICAL
  agent_type: codex
  surface: scribe-portable-init
  hot_entries_consulted:
  - PAT-SCRIBE-PAIN-CAPTURE-REFLEX-001
  - GHOST-SCRIBE-RAG-SEL-DIRECT-001
  - INV-F003
  l0_abstract: >
    TENOR INIT est durci par une preuve machine `scribe tenor-init` afin que les petits modeles ne reconstruisent plus l initialisation a la main ni n inventent les metriques SCRIBE.
  pourquoi: >
    Le test terrain a montre qu un petit modele pouvait lire Graphify, README et SCRIBE directement, affirmer que le skill init-tenor etait absent malgre un glob positif, puis produire un TENOR_HEADER narratif sans bootstrap, workflow ack ni requetes scribe-rag. Une regle textuelle ne suffit pas face a ce type de contradiction. La correction durable est donc de concentrer l initialisation dans une commande idempotente qui execute bootstrap, enregistre la presence agent, ack le workflow, interroge scribe-rag et imprime un bloc `SCRIBE-CHECK TENOR V4 -- MACHINE PROOF` verifiable.
  validations:
  - ".agent/workflow/scribe/scribe tenor-init --type cli: PASS, Status init VALID"
  - "python3 -m py_compile scribe_tenor_init.py scribe_install_templates.py: PASS"
  - "python3 -m unittest discover -s .agent/workflow/scribe/sel/tests -p test_scribe_bootstrap.py: PASS 6/6"
  - ".agent/workflow/scribe/scribe-rag gate: PASS eval 8/8"
  scribe_delta: JOURNAL-SCRIBE-TENOR-INIT-MACHINE-PROOF-20260616

- id: JOURNAL-SCRIBE-PAIN-CAPTURE-REFLEX-20260616
  date: 2026-06-16
  mode: CRITICAL
  agent_type: codex
  surface: scribe-memory-governance
  hot_entries_consulted:
  - PAT-SCRIBE-STRICT-CAUSAL-DENSITY-001
  - INV-F003
  l0_abstract: >
    Le reflexe SCRIBE est durci: ne pas viser un ratio abstrait, mais capturer 100% des douleurs reelles en SCAR exploitable et requeter ces cicatrices avant les travaux similaires.
  pourquoi: >
    Le risque identifie n est pas un manque cosmetique de densite causale, mais la perte de douleurs operationnelles si un bug, une regression, un rollback couteux ou un smoke visuel casse se termine par un simple journal. Sans cause_racine, resolution et test_binding, les futures sessions peuvent repeter la meme erreur. Le garde-fou doit donc etre immediat apres la douleur et actif avant la prochaine tache proche via scribe-rag query/explain/challenge.
  validations:
  - "Surfaces mises a jour: .agent/rules/scribe.md, README SCRIBE, AGENTS, scribe.md, friction-policy, init-tenor"
  - "Principe conserve: aucun SCAR/GHOST/PAT cosmetique pour gonfler le ratio causal"
  scribe_delta: PAT-SCRIBE-PAIN-CAPTURE-REFLEX-001 | JOURNAL-SCRIBE-PAIN-CAPTURE-REFLEX-20260616

- id: JOURNAL-BRVM-DATA-RESILIENCE-ABORTABLE-20260611
  date: 2026-06-11
  mode: CRITICAL
  agent_type: codex
  surface: market-data/brvm-routes
  hot_entries_consulted:
  - SCAR-SIDEBAR-FUNDAMENTALS-STALE-TICKER-001
  - VAC-BRVM-LIVE-TABLE-SELECTION-001
  - PAT-BRVM-DATA-RESILIENCE-001
  l0_abstract: >
    Les flux BRVM non-candles ont ete durcis autour d un contrat abortable: budgets source partages, fallback HTTP 200 compatible, headers cache/status et timeout sidebar fundamentals aligne.
  pourquoi: >
    La prochaine panne production probable n etait plus la serie daily candles, mais les donnees peripheriques BRVM de la sidebar. Le smoke avait montre fundamentals coupe a 12s cote client pendant que la route pouvait encore travailler. Ce delai trop court cassait l experience meme si la route etait capable de degrader. Le correctif devait donc traiter client et serveur ensemble: annulation reelle jusqu a undici, budgets interactifs bornes, fetch FR/EN fundamentals parallele, dividendes non bloquants et fallbacks JSON stables.
  validations:
  - "Next docs lus: Route Handlers, fetch, NextResponse"
  - "Graphify: fetchWithResilience relie live, fundamentals, capitalisation, indices, news et bonds dans la meme communaute BRVM"
  - "./node_modules/.bin/tsc --noEmit --pretty false: PASS"
  - "npx eslint routes BRVM + resilient-scraper + sidebar fetchers/hooks: PASS"
  - "npm run test:technical-analysis-config: PASS 41/41"
  - "npm run test:alerts-rail: PASS 21/21 apres escalation bwrap"
  - "curl fundamentals BOAB: HTTP 200 degrade, Cache-Control fallback, X-Cache-Status UNAVAILABLE"
  - "curl indices: HTTP 200 degrade, Cache-Control fallback, X-Cache-Status UNAVAILABLE"
  - "curl news: HTTP 200 succes, Cache-Control public, X-Cache-Status MISS"
  - "curl bonds: HTTP 200 fallback rapide, Cache-Control fallback, X-Cache-Status UNAVAILABLE"
  attention_future: >
    Pour ajouter ou modifier un flux BRVM, ne jamais reparer uniquement le hook ou uniquement la route. Le budget client, le budget source, le cache/SWR et le payload degrade doivent etre verifies ensemble, sinon une amelioration locale recree un faux echec sous latence africaine/mondiale.
  scribe_delta: PAT-BRVM-DATA-RESILIENCE-001 | JOURNAL-BRVM-DATA-RESILIENCE-ABORTABLE-20260611

- id: JOURNAL-TA-RIGHT-RAIL-SCREENERS-TRADINGVIEW-20260611
  date: 2026-06-11
  mode: STANDARD
  agent_type: codex
  surface: technical-analysis/right-rail-screeners
  hot_entries_consulted:
  - SCAR-TA-RIGHT-RAIL-TRADINGVIEW-STALK-FIRST-001
  l0_abstract: >
    Screeners right-rail reproduction used TradingView observation first, then adapted the existing local rail entry instead of creating a parallel surface.
  pourquoi: >
    TradingView showed Screeners as an existing right-rail entry opening a dense stock screener surface with filters, table columns and source-like context. The local product already had a screeners rail id, so creating a second entry would have duplicated navigation and increased drift. The correct move was to keep the rail contract, fix reliable pointer/keyboard activation, and replace the generic BRVM summary with a BRVM stock/bond screener panel.
  validations:
  - "TradingView MCP observation: hover tooltip Screeners, 44x44 right-rail button, Stock Screener overlay with filters and dense table"
  - "Local MCP smoke: activeEntry=screeners, aria-pressed=true, button 44x44, 12 equity rows, Bond Screener present, source/formula present"
  - "Keyboard smoke: focus Screeners then Enter opens Stock Screener"
  - "Follow-up fix: narrow sidebar table has no horizontal scroll; MCP measured wrapScrollWidth=clientWidth=250 and panelOverflowsX=false"
  - "Follow-up all-symbols: removed the 12-row cap; CDP measured rowCount=47, uniqueSymbols=47, no horizontal scroll"
  - "Follow-up filters: chips were static spans, now native buttons with aria-pressed; CDP clicked Price, Chg %, Mkt cap, P/E, EPS, Sector and Watchlist with observable row/order changes"
  - "Follow-up bonds: 0 obligations came from empty topBonds without a local fallback; the screener now fetches /api/market-data/brvm-bonds and CDP measured 5 obligations after load"
  - "MCP Chrome DevTools transport stayed closed; CDP /json/version and /json/list were verified before direct CDP smoke, no external browser test dependency added"
  - "./node_modules/.bin/tsc --noEmit: PASS"
  - "npm run lint: PASS"
  attention_future: >
    For the remaining TradingView right-rail icons, do not create new local navigation when a canonical rail id already exists. Observe TradingView first, decide ADAPTER_EXISTANT versus CREER_SURFACE, then validate activation with MCP Chrome DevTools.
  scribe_delta: JOURNAL-TA-RIGHT-RAIL-SCREENERS-TRADINGVIEW-20260611

- id: JOURNAL-TA-MARKET-NATIVE-TRIGGER-20260604
  date: 2026-06-04
  mode: STANDARD
  agent_type: codex
  surface: technical-analysis/components/market
  hot_entries_consulted:
  - PAT-PRD-FIRST-GATE-001
  - PAT-TA-FOOTER-NATIVE-CONTROLS-001
  - PAT-A11Y-DYNAMIC-PORTAL-SEARCHBOX-001
  - JOURNAL-TA-MARKET-CANONICAL-A11Y-20260603
  l0_abstract: >
    Market deep-analysis closed the currency and security identity folder by replacing the currency pseudo-button with a native trigger and keeping layout ownership unchanged.
  pourquoi: >
    Le dossier market etait deja canonique, donc le probleme restant etait la realite runtime du controle devise: un bouton visuel encode comme div role=button maintenait une dette de semantique, de ref et de clavier manuel. Le bon correctif etait de rendre le DOM honnete avec un vrai bouton, de garder la recherche/listbox existante, et de ne pas rouvrir les calculs de hauteur ou la logique de conversion. SecurityBadge devait seulement distinguer plus clairement les entrees inconnues du catalogue BRVM verifie.
  validations:
  - "Rollback snapshot market-realism-architecture-20260604-181023 created before edits"
  - "PRD market-realism-architecture status Implemented"
  - "npx eslint market components and useCurrencyState: PASS"
  - "sass _technical-analysis-final.scss: PASS"
  - "tsc --noEmit --pretty false: PASS"
  - "curl TA route: HTTP 200"
  - "Browser/CDP smoke: BUTTON trigger, dropdown open, usd filter returns USD only, option click closes dropdown, focus returns, overflow zero"
  attention_future: >
    Ne pas corriger une dette a11y market par des handlers clavier supplementaires si la semantique native existe. Si le layout casse autour du trigger devise, corriger le style local du bouton ou la chaine parent flex, jamais par calcul viewport.
  scribe_delta: PAT-TA-MARKET-NATIVE-TRIGGER-001 | JOURNAL-TA-MARKET-NATIVE-TRIGGER-20260604
  multi_agent_context:
    surface: technical-analysis/components/market
    generated_outputs_uncommitted: true
- id: JOURNAL-TA-FOOTER-NATIVE-CONTROLS-20260604
  date: 2026-06-04
  mode: STANDARD
  agent_type: codex
  surface: technical-analysis/components/footer
  hot_entries_consulted:
  - PAT-TA-DORMANT-HEADER-NO-REACTIVATION-001
  - PAT-PRICE-BADGE-TIME-LABEL-TRUTH-001
  - JOURNAL-TA-SIDEBAR-COMMON-CLOSURE-NEXT-20260604
  - SCAR-TA-STALE-CHROME-VIEWPORT-HEIGHT-001
  l0_abstract: >
    Footer deep-analysis closed the TA footer by replacing crude interactive semantics with native controls while leaving chart height ownership untouched.
  pourquoi: >
    Le risque visible du footer n etait pas une distribution verticale defectueuse mais une surface de commande faussement interactive: ranges en pseudo-boutons, bouton calendrier implicite, doublons de classes et elements decoratifs exposes. La correction realiste garde le footer dans son role compact: boutons natifs, etats ARIA, reset SCSS local et horloge BRVM conservee. Le gate TypeScript a aussi expose un ref currency encore type div alors que le composant actif rend un bouton; le contrat source a ete aligne au DOM reel sans cast. Le header dormant a ete revalide avant de passer au footer afin de ne pas confondre surface absente et surface a reactiver.
  validations:
